@node history "[4.0] History/Future    -  Past, Present, Future!"

   History
   ~~~~~~~
   v0.2
         Display showed the 24 hour time and the display type.
         Was not publicly released.
         No Bugs.

   v0.5
         Display showed the 24 hour & 12 hour time and the display type.
         Was not publicly released. Beta Tested on A600, A1200, A4000
         No Bugs.

   v0.9
         Completely re-wrote routines. Now displayed 24/12 Hour times,
         display type, Simple date (dd-mm-yy). Was not publicly released
         Beta Tested on A500+, A600, A1200, A1200 & A4000.
         No Bugs.

   v1.00
         Further cleansing of routines, made date display as though it
         was written (Tuesday, 17th December 1996) etc. added Kickstart
         routine, Wrote Documentation, Beta tested as v0.9
         *First public release*

   v1.02
         Optimised routines, added Workbench 1.3 routine, fixed 'White
         Italic' bug, wrote better documentation, added Installer script,
         "professionalised". No Bugs? Beta Tested as v0.9 + A500.
         *public release*

   v1.08
         All the little bugs fixed, removed WB 1.3 routine, removed various
         other bits. Added 'Processor' program.

   v1.24
         Ultra update! Totally re-wrote most routines, added and removed
         various parts. Updated installer, documents and assorted files.
         This one is strong (mmm...I like that minty flavour!). =o)

   Future:
   ~~~~~~~
   For future versions I may add the following features...

         Ę  Optionally display as GUI instead of CLI.

         Ę  Scrolling ANSI (It WILL look groovy!) =o)

         Ę  Logging, View Logging, Clear Logging

         Ę  Configuration File

         Ę  Your suggestions?


@endnode

